definitions: an act of making a place clean or tidy
an act of removing or putting an end to disorder, immorality, or crime

examples.text: a clean-up of the more open violence had begun

shortDefinitions: act of putting end to immorality or crime

definitions: the fourth position in a team's batting order, typically reserved for a power hitter likely to clear the bases by enabling any runners to score

examples.text: L.A.'s cleanup hitter smacked a fastball over the left-field fence
he garnered a certain amount of attention while playing right field and batting cleanup

shortDefinitions: fourth position in team's batting order
